Leader of a betrayed, enslaved and afflicted people under German occupation, Christian X of Denmark kept the spirit of freedom alive. He would have been a popular monarch in any country. He was a good soldier in a peaceful land, an ardent sportsman, a happy husband and father. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
